## Report issue

Note: please update ComfyUI first ([guide](https://docs.comfy.org/zh-CN/installation/update_comfyui)) and prepare required models. Desktop/Cloud ship stable builds; nightly-supported models may not be included yet, please wait for the next stable release.

- Cannot run / runtime errors: [ComfyUI/issues](https://github.com/comfyanonymous/ComfyUI/issues)
- UI / frontend issues: [ComfyUI_frontend/issues](https://github.com/Comfy-Org/ComfyUI_frontend/issues)

A professional Gestalt negative space logo of the subject. The design is a minimalist, high-contrast black and white graphic where the subject's form is defined entirely by solid, heavy black masses representing shadows, and pure white negative space representing highlights. There are no outlines and no fine lines. The visual style uses the principle of closure to suggest the full form, similar to the iconic panda logo style. The result is clean, bold, and optimized for 3D printing extrusion with no disconnected islands or thin artifacts.

A circular black and white emblem based on the input image. The central element is the exact high-contrast graphic provided in the reference image, unchanged. Surrounding this central graphic is a thick black inner circle ring. Outside of that is a slightly wider black outer circle ring. In the curved channel between the two concentric rings, the text 'PROPERTY OF XYZ' is rendered in a bold, clean, uppercase sans-serif font, following the curve of the circle. The entire design is a clean vector graphic on a solid white background.

widgets_values:
Click on the top-right corner of the node to open the [subgraph](https://docs.comfy.org/interface/features/subgraph) 
ðŸ‘‡

First, establish the layout: A professional circular stamp emblem defined by two thick, concentric black rings. In the white channel between these rings, curve the text 'Abhishek Does Stuff' in a bold, clean, uppercase sans-serif font along the top arc. Ensure the text is perfectly legible and geometric.

Next, fill the center of this circular frame with the subject rendered exactly as follows: A professional Gestalt negative space logo. The design is a minimalist, high-contrast black and white graphic where the subject's form is defined entirely by solid, heavy black masses representing shadows, and pure white negative space representing highlights. There are no outlines and no fine lines. The visual style uses the principle of closure to suggest the full form, similar to the iconic panda logo style.

Finally, ensure the entire combined image is a clean, flat, bold vector graphic optimized for 3D printing extrusion with no disconnected islands or thin artifacts. Strictly black and white (#000000 and #FFFFFF).
Unbypass this node to use a custom resolution for the output image. Otherwise, the output resolution will be based on Image 1.

Yes, I'm using the LightX2V LoRA created for the original Qwen Image model instead of the Qwen Image Edit 2511 version. In my opinion, it generates better outputs. If you disagree, just replace it with your own LoRA.
Enable this node only if you have Triton installed on your system.

Task: Transform the main subject of the input image into a high-contrast, iconic graphic design suitable for a logo. Subject: Isolate the primary subject on a solid, pure white background (#FFFFFF). Colors: Strictly limit the palette to solid black (#000000) and pure white (#FFFFFF) only. Absolutely no gray tones, shading, gradients, or textures. Style Technique: Render the subject using bold, disconnected black masses to define its primary structure, shadow areas, and visual weight. Crucially, utilize pure white negative space creatively to carve out essential internal details, highlights, and defining features within the black forms. Aesthetic Goal: The imagery should be minimalist, clean, and rely on the Gestalt principleâ€”using the high-contrast interplay of heavy black shapes against the white background to suggest the subject's full form without using continuous outlines. Preservation: Maintain the recognizable identity of the subject through the strategic placement and shape of these black and white masses.
